@startuml Execution_Flow
title EmuAVR - Execution Flow Diagram

start

:Initialize Bus & Devices;
note right
  - Create SRAM, EEPROM, Port, UART, SPI, TWI
  - Map devices to address ranges
end note

:Create CPU & Flash;
:Load HEX file to Flash;

:Create Clock;

:Call cpu.run(maxCycles);
note right
  Default: 10,000 cycles
end note

while (cycles < maxCycles AND keep_running_) is (yes)
  :Call cpu.step();
  note right
    - Fetch instruction from Flash
    - Decode and execute
    - Update registers/memory via Bus
    - Return cycles consumed
  end note
  
  :Emulate I/O devices;
  note right
    - Read/write Port, UART, SPI, TWI
    via Bus read/write operations
  end note
  
  :Emit JSON events;
  note right
    For debugger/UI communication
  end note
  
endwhile (no)

:Clock.tick(totalCycles);

:Return elapsed cycles;

:Print execution results;

stop

@enduml
